description: Up for sale or possible trade is my 32 foot (11'11" beam) 1979 Bayliner Yachts Conquest 3150 dual station (bridge inside and another up top). I got the boat last year on a trade and loved every moment with it. As did the rest of my family.  While i would love to keep her and like we did last year take her out every weekend it's just not in the cards for me right now. So i thought i'd put it here and see what happens. I did set the price a bit low from the NADA guide suggested price cause there are 3 relative issues that i understand affect such things. Those are.... 1.) She is still in winter storage with a $975 balance to put her back in the water and would need a slip. 2.) The port starter has a dead spot. So while it can be rotated and made to work it could use to be replaced or at least rebuilt 3.) The previous owner took apart the fresh water system for whatever reason... He said it was all there and just needed to be put back together and it looked like it was there but i always just brought water out with me to use for me and the kids and never worried about it. I did start cleaning it up last year and did even add 4 large solar panels to the front and a setup of 8 batteries that are tied to the bilge system but i put a sort of fuse panel on it with additional spots the plan had been to move the fridge and radio and lighting to those so i could leave the house batteries (which i did add 2 and replaced one bad one) purely for starting and running. Like i said we used it nearly every weekend right up until the end of October. Just dont have the time or cash or motivation for it right now and with health issues is kinda been put on the back burner. So i will entertain any reasonable offer. Like i said i have already come down quite a bit from what NADA suggested. Will also consider trades or partial trades for things like a camper, atv(s), or smaller boat and wave-runner, or just about anything my kids could enjoy that can be a little easier for me to manage. Again thank you for looking and since i guess i must note this no i'm not looking for help selling and will not ship it to your 3rd world country. (never thought i'd have to say that for for a 32ft boat lol)

description: Great condition, Low Hours. Currently at Winthrop Harbor, IL at North Point Marina in heated winter storage building. In 2000 the Regal 4160 was the Flagship of the Regal fleet (later called the 4260, then the 4460). But by any designation the Regal was a high-style luxury sport yacht with a spacious, well-arranged interior and a particularly innovative cockpit layout. The 2000 Regal 4160  rides on a wide-beam deep-V hull with propeller pockets. The 4160's aggressive profile owes much to a gracefully integrated bow pulpit and a unique fore-and-aft arch design. Boarding from one of two transom gates, one is struck by the cockpit configuration,  the elevated bridge deck is huge with a large U-shaped settee and table opposite the helm. This arrangement creates a very social layout since most of the guest seating is centered near the double-wide helm seat rather than aft as is the case on most express cruisers. Lots of room on deck. Easily accommodates 10 adults. The 4160's plush two-stateroom interior features cabins with pocket doors for privacy (rather than curtains). Each cabin has it's own head and shower. Additional features include a walk-through windshield, cockpit wet bar, a power-assist windshield vent, foredeck sun pad, large transom storage locker, two refrigerators, ice maker, 2 burner stove, microwave, brand new JVC Bluetooth stereo with Subwoofer/Amp with Bose speakers. Transom shower. Windlass anchor. All interior and exterior replaced with LED bulbs for no heat and little power draw. Stainless davit that mounts to rear platform to lift wave runners/Jetski/dingy. Powered by twin Mercruiser 8.2L inboards. Only 365 hours engines and boat since new! Cruising Speed 18Max Speed 27 Dimensions Nominal Length 41 Length Overall 44.3 Length on Deck 40.8 Max Bridge Clearance 10.58 Max Draft 2.9 Beam 14 Cabin Headroom 6.5 Weights Dry Weight 20375 Accommodations Single Berth s4 Cabins 2 Heads 2 Never smoked on. Very clean, no rips/tears in any cushions.  75% of Canvas and glass was replaced last year. All canvas in glass in great shape.  Everything works.  Have last survey which was done in May of 2016. No issues. Not interested in trades and will not reply to brokers looking to sell my boat. Full specs and more info available on request.
title: Regal 4160 Commodore
